feed.title: Radiation level at Hoogwoud, Netherlands
feed.description:
This is a home brew geiger counter with a SBM-20 tube. The SBM-20 is sensitive for hard-β and γ radiation. The 16F628 microcontroller counts the pulses from the tube and transmits the counted value every minute via RS232 to my PC. A small self written script creates a logfile and uploads the data to this feed. 

The sensor is located inside the house . The SBM-20 tube is mostly unshielded so air can circulate around it. In this situation it is also possible for the tube to detect hard-β (>250keV).
Although the data is trustful, keep in mind that this is not an official site. So use it for informative purposes only.

01-11-2012:
The QNAP NAS is now taking care of logging and sent the data to COSM.

21-03-2013:
Datalogging is now done by a t5700 thin client running on debian linux. Also the circuit will be redesigned for a SI-22G geiger tube which is more sensitive than the SBM-20.

07-04-2011:
Added a half hour (actually 32 mins) average.
